<TD><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica"><FONT SIZE=+1>Consumer Reports Rates
Wireless Phones and Services</FONT></FONT></B></TD>

<TD></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD></TD>

<TD><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">A worksheet in the September (P. 24) issue
and on Consumer Reports Online, www.ConsumerReports.org, helps compute
which combination of cell phone and service costs less. The comprehensive
report on cellular phones and phone services also includes a look at: the
pros and cons of analog vs. digital handsets; a comparison of how Omnipoint,
Sprint, and Bell Atlantic performed in one metropolitan area; the new plans
such as AT &amp; T One Rate and prepaid cellular; and the cost of being
connected in the 15 largest U.S. wireless markets. (<A HREF="http://biz.yahoo.com/bw/980817/consumers__3.html">YAHOO</A>)
- (<A HREF="http://www.ConsumerReports.org/Special/CurrentIssue/index.html">CONSUMER
