<TD><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica"><FONT SIZE=+1>Lucent Gets Acquisition
Green Light</FONT></FONT></B></TD>

<TD></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD></TD>

<TD><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">Since its spin-off two years ago from
AT&amp;T, Lucent has been restricted by the terms of its separation from
the telecommunications giant to acquiring smaller companies. But starting
in October, Lucent will be able to use the "pooling of interests" method
of deal making, an accounting method that will allow for stock-swap takeovers,
which ultimately lower the cost of making acquisitions. Analysts almost
unanimously agree that Lucent's No. 1 takeover target will be Ascend Communications.
(<A HREF="http://www.news.com/News/Item/Textonly/0,25,25361,00.html?pfv">NEWS.COM</A>)</FONT></TD>

<TD></TD>
</TR>

