<TR>
<TD></TD>

<TD><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica"><FONT SIZE=+1>Justice Departments Says
U.S. Manufacturers&nbsp;<BR>
May Share Y2K Plans</FONT></FONT></B></TD>

<TD></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD></TD>

<TD><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">The Department of Justice told manufacturers
they could share information on resolving Year 2000 computer issues without
running afoul of antitrust laws.&nbsp; The National Association of Manufacturers
had sought approval of a plan to let its 14,000 member companies and their
computer services suppliers exchange data on fixing the computer date problem.
(<A HREF="http://dailynews.yahoo.com/headlines/tc/story.html?s=v/nm/19980817/tc/y2k_1.html">YAHOO</A>)</FONT></TD>

