to Fight Union on Performance Targets</FONT></FONT></B></TD>

<TD></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD></TD>

<TD><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">CEO Solomon Trujillo said that the only
way his company can beat upstart rivals is by being first with new services.&nbsp;
To do that, U S WEST wants to tie workers' salaries to aggressive performance
targets. (<A HREF="http://www.bloomberg.com/news2.cgi?T=technews.ht&s=581612911">BLOOMBERG
TECHNOLOGY NEWS</A>)</FONT></TD>

