<TD><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica"><FONT SIZE=+1>Ericsson to Boost Role
in Brazil</FONT></FONT></B></TD>

<TD></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD></TD>

<TD><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">Telefon AB L.M. Ericsson submitted a bid
of $640 million to purchase shares in its Brazilian subsidiary, which it
presently does not own. Currently owning 95 percent of the voting shares
and 51 percent of the total shares, Ericsson's stake in Ericsson SA will
grow to 99 percent if the bid is accepted. The bid will remain open until
Sept. 16. Ericsson had $1.25 billion in 1997 sales in Brazil. (<A HREF="http://interactive.wsj.com/edition/current/articles/SB903365420714663500.htm">WALL
ST. JOURNAL</A>)</FONT></TD>

